		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've read that the Japanese NTSC color saturation is mapped slightly different than US TVs. And that viewing such Japanese specific setup equipment will yield slightly lesser saturation on a US display. But from what I've read, it's not a huge difference. 
<br />
<br /> With that said, wiki states YUV and YIQ use the same transform for RGB into their color space. If that's true, and what I've read about NTSC and NTSC-J, then what's the correct transform multiplication matrix for NTSC-J YUV/YIQ?
<br />
<br /> TmEE: once I get an amp setup for RGB on the PCE, I can check that out on the scope. The composite output uses separate DACs than the RGB output, but from what I've seen on the composite output - the Y channel is extremely sharp (very sharp rise/fall edge transitions). It's possible that there's something different about the RGB DAC outputs.

		

		</td>
